                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.24/386a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Casablanca</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stanton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-30T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 30, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>113. Please urgently request Reed of Socony Vacuum<note n="45" xml:id="d268fn45"
                        >A. G. Reed, General Manager of the Socony-Vacuum Oil Company at
                        Casablanca.</note> to endeavor to check through his organization a report
                    which has reached the Department to the effect that under German pressure French
                    authorities in Tunisia have advanced for use of Axis forces in North Africa
                    considerable quantities of petroleum products, particularly from French naval
                    reserve at Bizerte, as well as a number of tanks and other equipment.</p>
                <p>The subject<note n="45a" xml:id="d268fn45a">Lt. Col. Robert A. Solborg, observer
                        for the Military Intelligence Division, War Department, in North
                        Africa.</note> of the Department’s telegram No. 21 of January 29<note n="46"
                        xml:id="d268fn46">Not printed.</note> might also be consulted in this
                    regard.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
